{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπισκοπ-έω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> -σκέψομαι, later <b>-σκοπήσω</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Babrius Fabularum Scriptor 103.8: \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<i>aorist</i> -εσκεψάμην, later <b>-εσκόπησα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Herm.” 44, 59 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἐπέσκεμμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀρχαίης ἰητρικῇς” 14, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Epinomis” 990a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also in <i>passive</i> sense, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Caelo” 299a10, “PA” 692a18 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>look upon</b> or <b>at, inspect, observe</b>, ἱστορίας καὶ τἆλλα ἔγγραφα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Milet.” 3.155 (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>] (also in <i>middle</i>, ἐ. τὸ περίχωμα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PLille” 1v 27 (3rd c.BC), etc.)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <b>regard</b>, τἄμ᾽ ἐ. κακά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 869 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of tutelary gods, Θηβαΐας ἐπισκοποῦντ᾽ ἀγυιάς, of Bacchus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1136 (Lyric poetry); Ἴλιον.. ἐπισκοπεῖ σεμνὸς Ποσειδῶν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 1414, compare “Ph.” 661 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὦ Δῆμ᾽, ἐναργῶς ἡ θεός σ᾽ ἐπισκοπεῖ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1173, compare 1186 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also of a ruler, ἐ. τὴν πολιτείαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 506b, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 4.6 (so in _middle_, θαμὰ ἐπεσκοπεῖτο ἡμᾶς\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>observed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Lysis” 207a): followed by Relat., ἐ. καὶ ἀναμετρήσαντες ὅσῳ ἐλάσσων ὁ χῶρος γέγονε 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.109; ἐ. πῶς ἔχει 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 451c; τόδε ἐπίσκεψαι εἴ τι λέγω [prev. author] “Phd.” 87b, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.1.22; πότερον.. ἤ.. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 518a; τίς εἴη.. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.2.4, compare “Smp.” 1.12 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. μή.. <b>take care</b> lest, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Heb.12.15. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3>. <b>visit</b>, ὦ θάνατε, νῦν μ᾽ ἐπίσκεψαι μολών [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 854 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>visit</b> as a friend (ironically), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 9.12 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; especially <b>visit</b> the sick, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.2.25, “Mem.” 3.11.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the physician, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 4.2.4 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 59.56, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 11.2, 14.633:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, εὐνὴν ὀνείροις οὐκ ἐπισκοπουμένην <b>visited</b> not by dreams, i.e. sleepless, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 13. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3>. of a general, <b>inspect, review</b>, τὰς τάξεις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.3.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ ὅπλα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cyr.” 6.3.21, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 296. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3>. <b>consider, reflect, meditate</b>, ὅ τι ἂν μέλλῃς ἐρεῖν, πρότερον ἐπισκόπει τῇ γνώμῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.41 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also ἐ. πρός τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 924d; περί τινος [prev. author] “Prt.” 348d, +others, 1st c.AD: Cebes Philosophus 35.5; ὑπέρ τινος 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.15.2; σαυτὸν ἐ. ὅστις εἴης 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.2.24; ἐ. τίς.., ποία τις.. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1274b32; πότερον.. [prev. work] 1276b16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, <b>examine with oneself</b>, <b>meditate</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 91d; εἰς τὸ ἀληθὲς ἐ. τι [prev. author] “Phlb.” 61e, compare 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 219.8, 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 46:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, <i>perfect</i> (see.above). <br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3>. <b>exercise the office of</b> ἐπίσκοπος, variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.1Pet.5.2. \">NT</a>]","strongNumber":"G1983","accentedUnicode":"ἐπισκοπέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1909","matchingForm":"ἐπί","stepTransliteration":"epi","gloss":"upon/to/against","_zh_tw_Gloss":"在","_es_Gloss":"sobre/a/contra ","_zh_Gloss":"在"},{"strongNumber":"G1985","matchingForm":"ἐπίσκοπος","stepTransliteration":"episkopos","gloss":"overseer","_zh_tw_Gloss":"監督","_es_Gloss":"supervisor","_zh_Gloss":"监督"},{"strongNumber":"G4648","matchingForm":"σκοπέω","stepTransliteration":"skopeō","gloss":"to watch out","_zh_tw_Gloss":"小心","_es_Gloss":"estar alerta","_zh_Gloss":"小心"}],"shortDef":"to see to, care for; to serve as an overseer oversee","mediumDef":"to see to, care for; to serve as an overseer oversee <br /><b>to look at, inspect;</b>, <i>metaphorically</i> <b>to be circumspect, heedful,</b> <ref='Heb.12.15'>Heb. 12:15;</ref> <b>to oversee, to exercise the office of</b> <greek>ἐπισκοπος</greek>, <ref='1Pe.5.2'>1Pet. 5:2</ref>*","stepGloss":"to oversee/care for","stepTransliteration":"episkopeō","count":2,"_es_Definition":"ocuparse, cuidar ; administrar","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 關照, 看管 (來 12:15)<br>2) 監督, 照顧 (彼前 5:2)","_zh_Definition":"1) 关照, 看管 (来 12:15)<br>2) 监督, 照顾 (彼前 5:2)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"chú xem; oi chừng. ἐπί (G1909) + σκοπέω (G4648)","_zh_tw_Gloss":"照管, 要細心照顧","_es_Gloss":"supervisar/cuidar","_zh_Gloss":"照管, 要细心照顾"}]}